713933f-a.title: Manhattan: 57th Street (West) - 11th Avenue
713933f-a.text:
West 57th Street (center, left to right), at Eleventh Ave.
(left), as viewed in a northward direction from 56th Street and
across the future site of the Sheffield Farms milk plant, showing
the diagonal rock cut roadway of the New York Central Railroad
tracks which will pass beneath this structure and continue in a
northward direction to the 60th Street yards (center, background).
Completion of this phase of the West Side Project will eliminate
the use of the street bed of the Ave. for Railroad purposes as observed
on the right at the base of the I.R.T. power plant between 58th and
59th Streets.
1937.
ift of New york Central System
Publicity Bureau.
CREDIT LINE IMPERATIVE ON ALL REPRODUCTIONS.

713934f-a.title: Manhattan: 57th Street (West) - 11th Avenue
713934f-a.text:

construction and occupying the westerly portion of the 57th to 56th
Street.Buildinga appearing at the left will shortly be razed to permit

Nroadbed of the New York Central Railroad beneath the steel,veering on

733565f-a.title: West Side Improvement Project.
733565f-a.text:
West Side Improvement Project: A northward view from under West
57th Street, showing the rock bed of the enclosed Railroad tracks
progressing towards the 60th Street yards on the westerly side of
Eleventh Ave., after paralleling the easterly side of same from 35th
Street. At the left appears the I.R.T. power house on the west side
of Eleventh Ave., between 58th and 59th Streets.
July 24, 1937.
Dift of New York Central System
Publicity Bureau.
CREDIT LINE IMPERATIVE ON ALL REPRODUCTIONS.
